The paper discusses tracking methods, which are commonly studied in robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV). The use of random finite sets (RFSs) is also relevant to control systems (cs.SY). The algorithms derived in the paper involve probabilistic reasoning, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
